title: 797-A
statement: A. k-Factorizationtime limit per test2 secondsmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstandard inputoutputstandard outputGiven a positive integern, findkintegers (not necessary distinct) such that all these integers are strictly greater than1, and their product is equal ton.InputThe first line contains two integersnandk(2 ≤n≤ 100000,1 ≤k≤ 20).OutputIf it's impossible to find the representation ofnas a product ofknumbers, print-1.Otherwise, printkintegers in any order.
